import React, { useState, useEffect } from "react"; import { Link, useNavigate } from "react-router-dom"; import { ref, get } from "firebase/database"; // Assuming you're using Firebase. import { useAuth } from "../context/AuthContext"; import { db } from "../fireba/firebase"; import profile from "./avatar.png"; import setting from "./settings.png"; import change from "./cigarette.png"; import multipe from "./multiple-users-silhouette.png"; import friend from "./friends.png"; export default function Dashboard() { const [error, setError] = useState(""); const [userData, setUserData] = useState({ name: "", age: "", country: "" }); const { currentUser, logout } = useAuth(); const navigate = useNavigate(); useEffect(() => { const fetchUserData = async () => { try { const dbRef = ref(db, "compte"); const snapshot = await get(dbRef); if (snapshot.exists()) { setUserData(snapshot.val()); } else { console.error("No data found"); } } catch (error) { console.error("Error fetching data:", error); } }; fetchUserData(); }, []); async function handleLogout() { setError(""); try { await logout(); navigate("/login"); } catch { setError("Failed to log out"); } } return (
